                    "---",
                    "",
                    "",
                    "Client supports the preselect property on a completion item."
                ],
                "meta": [],
                "type": {
                    "kind": "optional",
                    "type": {
                        "kind": "builtin",
                        "value": "boolean"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "name": "resolveSupport",
                "documentation": [
                    "```lua",
                    "(field) lsp.ClientCompletionItemOptions.resolveSupport: (lsp.ClientCompletionItemResolveOptions)?",
                    "```",
                    "",
                    "---",
                    "",
                    "",
                    "Indicates which properties a client can resolve lazily on a completion",
                    "item. Before version 3.16.0 only the predefined properties `documentation`",
                    "and `details` could be resolved lazily.",
                    ""
                ],
                "meta": [],
                "type": {
                    "kind": "optional",
                    "type": {
                        "kind": "typereference",
                        "value": "lsp.ClientCompletionItemResolveOptions"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "name": "snippetSupport",
                "documentation": [
                    "```lua",
                    "(field) lsp.ClientCompletionItemOptions.snippetSupport: boolean?",
                    "```",
                    "",
                    "---",
                    "",
                    "",
                    "Client supports snippets as insert text.",
                    "",
                    "A snippet can define tab stops and placeholders with `$1`, `$2`",
                    "and `${3:foo}`. `$0` defines the final tab stop, it defaults to",
                    "the end of the snippet. Placeholders with equal identifiers are linked,",
                    "that is typing in one will update others too."
                ],
                "meta": [],
                "type": {
                    "kind": "optional",
                    "type": {
                        "kind": "builtin",
                        "value": "boolean"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "name": "tagSupport",
                "documentation": [
                    "```lua",
                    "(field) lsp.ClientCompletionItemOptions.tagSupport: (lsp.CompletionItemTagOptions)?",
                    "```",
                    "",
                    "---",
                    "",
                    "",
                    "Client supports the tag property on a completion item. Clients supporting",
                    "tags have to handle unknown tags gracefully. Clients especially need to",
                    "preserve unknown tags when sending a completion item back to the server in",
                    "a resolve call.",
                    ""
                ],
                "meta": [],
                "type": {
                    "kind": "optional",
                    "type": {
                        "kind": "typereference",
                        "value": "lsp.CompletionItemTagOptions"
                    }
                }
            }
        ],
